Chevening has announced the opening of applications for its Scholarships for the 2023/2024 academic year on August 2.
A notice on the scholarship administrator’s verified Twitter page reads: “We are thrilled to announce the dates for this year’s applications.
“Applications will open on 2 August and close on 1 November.”
The scholarship is funded by the UK government through the Foreign, Commonwealth and Development Office (FCDO) and partner organisations.
It is aimed at developing global leaders and since 1983 has enabled over 50,000 professionals, including many Nigerians, to study in the UK.
Beneficiaries of Chevening scholarship enjoy fully paid scholarship to study one-year Master’s programme at UK universities.
